CREATE A DECK OF CARDS AND PRINT OUT THE HEARTS:

A playing card, such as the queen of spades has both
a pip value and a suit value:

    pip value = 12
   suit value = spade

(Our usage of the word "pip" is correct; see you dictionary.)

To represent a card in a machine, we create a structure with
two members:

   struct card {
      int    pips;
      char   suit;
   };

A deck of cards is represented by an array of struct cards,
with the array size equal to 52.

In this program, we create a deck of cards, and then we print
out the hearts just to see that everything is working
as it should.
